"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by PRS for Music [FBB0070]&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nPRS for Music &#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nResponse to the CMS Committee’s questions&#xa0;What should the BBC be for and what should be the purpose of public service broadcasting?\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWhat scope, scale and remit should the BBC have? \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nHow have the BBC’s commercial activities during the current Charter fitted with the BBC\n’s public purposes and have the achieved an adequate return for \nlicence\n fee payers?  What should the aims, scope and scale of such activities beyond 2016?\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWhat role should the BBC play in developing technology and new ways of distributing content?\n  \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nHow should the BBC be funded beyond 2016? How should the BBC be governed, regulated \nand held accountable beyond 2016?  \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nDecember 2013\n&#xa0;\n"